<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900809-0132</DOCNO><DOCID>900809-0132.</DOCID><HL>   Tyco Toys Bids for Rest of Nasta</HL><DATE>08/09/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   TTOY NAS</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)</IN><LP>   MOUNT LAUREL, N.J. -- Tyco Toys Inc. said it will offer $1a share for the approximately 1.3 million shares outstandingof Nasta International Inc. that Tyco doesn't already own.   Tyco said it would commence next week a tender offer toshareholders of Nasta, a New York-based maker of lower-pricedtoys. Tyco, which recently increased its Nasta ownership to74% from 63%, said it has withdrawn a previously announcedmerger proposal.</LP><TEXT>   The toy maker also said it intends to offer to exchange anew issue of Tyco 10-year 8% subordinated debentures forNasta's $7.5 million principal amount of 12% convertiblesubordinated debentures outstanding. Agreement in principlehas been reached for the exchange of more than $3 million ofthe Nasta debentures.</TEXT></DOC>